Standards-Version: 3.5.2

Package: libggz-dev
Architecture: any
Section: devel
Depends: libggz0 (= ${Source-Version}), libc6-dev (>= 2.2.1-1)
Description: Development files for the GGZ library libggz
 If you want to use libggz for your own programs, you
 will have to install this package.
 It contains, among others, the header file <ggz.h>.

Package: libggz0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Replaces: libeasysock
Conflicts: libeasysock
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: GGZ base library
 The libggz library contains functionality for lists,
 configuration files, XML parsing, and networking.
 The network parts have been taken over from the easysock
 library.

